  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrates host reconnaissance to hardcoded Discord webhook",
  "details": "The package's postinstall lifecycle hook runs index.js on every `npm install`. index.js collects OS platform/arch, hostname, OS username, private IP addresses (from os.networkInterfaces), public IP (fetched from https://api.ipify.org), the package name, current working directory, and a timestamp, then POSTs the collected data to a hardcoded Discord webhook at discord.com/api/webhooks/. The package name pattern (fury_frontend-*) and inflated version number (99.9.6) are consistent with a dependency-confusion lure targeting an internal scope.",
